review:
EDIT: I'm updating my review after a patch than change a lot the whole balancement of the game. I would say than Child of Ault for my eyes is almost twice as good as before. Now your units are very effective, you can cast many of them (before they go and die soon, so slingshot was the only afforbable way to combat) and I'm experimenting mixing tanks and long range units.

Slingshot is still useful, but not as much as before. With this change I was able to progress more in the game, and there are quite nice environments later. Can't say the overall lenght (the difficulty jumped out after a while), from the map doens't seems huge but not sure if it's the only map avaliable, if something drive you to replay previous locations as any of them has a star ranking.

In any case, very promising improvements. Nice feedback too, it's ever a good thing when a dev listen to users.

---

At the moment is missing a review of this game in english, and the description itself is not very clear about contents.

Child of Ault is a tower defense game, with the classical slingshot fighting seen in other games, but with some differences:

1) your shots could use mana to cast magic;
2) you can summon character to defense your tower;
3) you've a map with lot of locations to beat during the campaign;
4) you're going to grow unlocking new spells and summon;
5) the game try to add a story and some characters;
6) there are sort of boss fights.

All those elements are interesting, in my opinion. Unfortunately in game strategy weights 20% where slingshots is 80%, and as an action game is not good enough to stay close to QuiVR or archery in The Lab. That said, Child of Ault is not a bad product (at least for VR standards) and delivers some variety and contents. With more strategy I would be way more happier, but could be a game to consider if you like this kind, maybe discounted.
